reviews.text: I've been to Kilkenny many times. This was my first in the castle. It was amazing. Great guides from room to room. Great explanations of the rooms too. View from the castle is even better!

Absolutely beautiful castle and gardens. Very accessible from Kilkenny town. Extremely interesting history of the castle which is easily obtained. Wonderful little cafe with a great variety of food and beautiful cakes and very helpful staff. Wonderful day out for all ages.

Beautiful grounds!! Really nicely kept.

The cafe is useless though- waited to be served for a good 5 minutes but no one came even though we could Clearly see them just talking out back.
Great castle in the heart of Kilkenny. A step back in time.  Nice little tea room in basement of castle.  Beautiful grounds. Definitely worth a visit!

We didn't take a tour but did see the video in the theater at the base of the tower. Impressive history. The sandwich/bakery shop was excellent. What we did love was the specialty shops across the street and carriage yard. There were linen spreads and cool looking wooden furniture.
Beautiful and historic location hidden in amongst relatively new developments.
Interesting place and quite cheap too. Must visit it if you go to Kilkenny.
Very surprising and fabulous place to visit, right in the heart of Kilkenny. A must see.
This was a fabulous find. It gives you a sense of the time period and we had plenty of time to roam around during the self guided tour.

This was a wonderful experience for me. It brought history alive. Its amazing to think that somehow I had family who lived and survived over the ages. I found the staff welcoming and helpful. The garden is a relaxing and beautiful experience. We'll worth a visit.

Super cute toy and gift shop in Kilkenny. Games, decorations, toys for infants, toddlers and little ones. The shop also had a few jewelery pieces (unicorn pendant!), and a little bargain bin corner filled with sale items. Definitely make this one of your shop stops while visiting Kilkenny.
Lovely store.

The experience is always uplifting.  The decor and ambience do it for me, plus the fact that there's always something new that seems to have been chosen with ME in mind.  My Max Benjamin candle and vintage cards are sparking joy.
Lovely shop with unusual items. Only negative can be late opening in the morning
Anne is a delight and super helpful! Georgeous shop
Beautiful Cathedral 162 years old being tastily restored😉
Beautiful but unbelievablely cold

Well worth a visit
One of the oldest Cathedrals around
Very well maintained
Well worth a visit , food excellent well presented, staff,nothing seems to be a problem to them.

The cathedral for the diocese of Ossory. Well worth a visit for anybody interested in religious architecture, it was built in 1847, a recent edition was the installation of a gold ceiling above the altar. Otherwise it's a fully functioning Cathedral hosting masses, weddings, funerals, confirmations and confessions etc.
Had lunch in the Design Centre Cafe from a fixed menu. The choices were very limited but the food was good. Service could have been more attentive especially with refilling drinks.
Piped in here the other day just as great as ever.LOVELY LUNCH
Very nice selection of artistic Irish gifts. It is expensive but they are different than your typical tourist souvenir. Very helpful workers!

This is a review for the Kilkenny Design Centre Cafe, which is above the Design Centre store.

The cafe extends the entire length of this classic stone building, and on sunny days is flooded with light from the circular windows that overlook the Design Centre courtyard. 

There's always a great selection of hot food and beautiful cakes, and there's plenty of choice for vegetarians.

Whilst a hot meal represents good value, if you just get a plain coffee and a cake it's pretty expensive. Still, he Design Centre remains my favourite spot for a Saturday-morning snack.
It is a really nice shop with loads of brilliant Irish designers' work. Purchasing those products is the best way to support Irish designers.
Beautiful late 19th century parish church with very interesting history. Well worth a visit
Very well cared for church
Its a beautiful church at the top of Johns Street it has a beautiful scenery and its a fabulous church gor a wedding

Worth a visit for tourists interested in ecclesiastical architecture, built between 1903-1908, it is the parish church of St. John the Evangelist. Still offers catholic services, often including choir. Parking available across the road in MacDonagh Junction or the Railway station or John's Green.
A truly beautiful Church
Small and friendly museum. The smart audioguide is included in the 8 euros ticket. Lovely staff.
Really loved it! Definitely go on the guided tour as it really brings to life the whole story of the city. Our guide Pat was incredibly knowledgeable and we had a fantastic time
Beautiful interesting Museum in heart of Kilkenny City. The staff are friendly and helpful. I’ve also had the opportunity to attend some evening event. Such a lovely setting in a beautiful venue

Fantastic & Fascinating insight into medieval Kilkenny. Staff were lovely, very helpful. Strongly recommend the guided tour which for us was delivered by the very learned and affable Pat. Very patient with us as we had two kids running around, he kept them going with the Lego Hunt and delivered the history to us in Humerous, enthusiastic fashion. Thank you again guys. Pat gets an extra nod for knowing who Lamb of God are.
Interesting but not worth the entrance fee. It could be improved by providing more information on medieval life in Kilkenny.

Could not fault "Sol"! Ate here two weeks ago, the food was fantastic, staff lovely and very attentive. Great experience. Book in advance so you won't be disappointed.👍
Local fresh ingredients beautifully cooked. I love this place but I'd love it more if the menu changed a bit more regularly.
An excellent surprise. Typical Irish food and tasty beers & wine. Lovely atmosphere.
Excellent food. Delicious. Small place
Delicious! Cute restaurant tucked away on a side street. The spiced carrot soup is a must.

My husband and I stopped off here on our way back north from Cork. We booked a special rate for room and an evening meal. The room was fabulous, and featured a spacious lounge suite as well as an extremely comfy bed. We were disappointed, however, with the dining experience, both dinner and breakfast. After being crammed into a corner we hoped would provide some privacy, we were immediately flanked by a large party who were louder than we would have liked. We were told we were going to have a choice from the a la carte menu, and were presented with a two course menu with limited options. My husband had to go to the reception desk to query the issue, and by the time we had managed to get to the stage of working out which was the correct menu for us, he was quite flustered. Not a good start to what should have been a relaxing meal. Starters both featured salads with lack lustre iceberg lettuce, and I ordered a main course of pumpkin pasta, which arrived on my plate with a consistency of cardboard. It was a struggle to eat! My husbands lamb shoulder was - thank goodness - nice and tender. Overall we found the service and food below par for a four star hotel. I have stayed in 3 star hotels with better service and food. While the rooms are gorgeous and very comfy I would recommend guests eat at one of the many nearby restaurants.
Lovely hotel in central location. Rooms are spacious and well decorated. The staff are polite, friendly and helpful. Food is excellent. Well done to all concerned. We had a super break .

Very old hotel in need of refurbishment. The only elevator in the hotel was out of order.

We had a standard room. Room decor is nice but only a small king bed.  No double glazing on the hotel window so you can lots of noise from the street. Only two plugs nowhere near the bed. No air conditioning. You can't turn on or off the radiators. our room only had a small bathroom with only a small shower.

We stayed here for two nights midweek at the end of October 2018. We had a warm welcome from all the staff and everyone was really helpful. The hotel is lovely and our deluxe room was brilliant. Lovely little touches throughout the hotel which made our stay fantastic. Kilkenny town is great and very friendly. This is my new favourite place and would love to return again soon.
The bar is still a real gem but rest of hotel needs an overhaul. Rooms too hot and stuffy, heating system noisy. Used to be a great place to stay...maybe it will again

Stopped in here today for a quick drink. I'm a whiskey drinker and they have a huge range which is always a good thing. Drinks menu shows their range. Only thing is they have no prices on the whiskey list. Which I found very strange. Apart from that. The staff are friendly and it's a lovely pub.
Genuinely think my boyfriend loves this place more than he loves me. Absolute gem of a place such a lovely atmosphere with a fantastic history. Would give 50 stars if I could!
Came in for a few quiet pints, but ended up having a great evening listening to the music & stayed longer than i had planned. Good craic, lovely pints & great atmosphere. Cracking pub🎵🍻🎶☘🎵🍻🎶☘
Delicious food. We had different dishes which were all perfect. Here we like to come again.
Great atmosphere, large pub, does food, wide selection of beer and gins. Good music every night. Excellent staff.
Wonderful meal here at Zuni this evening. Arrived having not booked, on my own. The restaurant was packed but they squeezed me in. A great atmosphere. Highly recommend.
Fantastic. Great food. Lovely atmosphere. Professional staff. Well priced. Highly recommended.
Excellent meal, polite and friendly staff, a place to remember - to come back too!
Stayed here on our first trip around Ireland. Lovely place to stay. Amazing breakfast in the Gorgeous restaurant.
The food is absolutely excellent in a most pleseant setting. Kilkenny is a wonderful venue to visit.

Best restaurant in Fairbanks! Beautiful scenery along the river. I had the blackened halibut which was amazing and my dad got the red deer and it was also delicious. We plan on returning again before we leave Fairbanks. We also shared the elk sliders and they were very tasty. The apple pie was good.

Definitely not worth the craze. The service is good. The food is average. The Elk burger is nothing to rave about; it was too salty and overcooked. The parking lot during the winter is a death trap. With the prices they charge, I was not satisfied.

We went to the Pump House for dinner on the last night of our vacation in Fairbanks because we have read numerous reviews of this place and wanted to try it out. 

The service was absolutely fantastic. Our waitress was very energetic and talkative. She gave us a good rundown of the menu. 

We specifically avoided other “ordinary” choices on the menu since you could easily get steaks and king crabs anywhere else. We wanted to try something exotic and different. As a result, we ended up ordering the elk meatloaf and clams with reindeer sausage.

To be honest, I could not tell any difference between beef and elk and reindeer meat. The reindeer sausage tasted just like any other sausage but there were only a total of 4 small pieces of sausage in our plate. The elk meatloaf was the same as any other meatloaf we had before.

We were not impressed probably because of the high expectations we had when we walked in there. The service was fantastic, the vibe and atmosphere of the interior decor was one of the kind but the meal itself was alright.

Certainly a fine place for dining choice in the area. We ordered the cod and the deer meat, both are good choices. The waitress was super warm and enthusiastic. Also loved the decor with a feel of local culture.

Great dining experience! Reindeer steak was delicious, tender, and cooked just right. The creme brulee was light and delicious. Highly recommend for a special occasion for the price is at the higher, fine dining range. My wife and I will definitely be returning again.

Very interesting tour. The guide (Helen) has great sense of humor keeping us all entertained.
The cave is cold all year round (9 degrees) so make sure you wrap up warm!

Absolutely fascinating place, the guide was brilliant, knew a lot about the caves as well as local history which our kids (10 & 8) found interesting. When we visited they had no card machine so might be worth checking before you visit. Thanks for a really interesting visit.

Excellent value for only fiver euro an adult and the 4 year old was free. She the 4 year old said to me this will take ages but she was pleasantly surprised that it didn't feel like a long time for her or us. The guide was knowledgeable and humorous.
Plus they waiting for us as we were a little bit slower than most going down the steps so we could hear the stories.
Lovely place with tour.  Would have loved more time to look at the cave after talk was given by guide
Affordable. Good tour. 700 steps, so not for faint of lung. Knowledgeable guide. BV RECOMMEND!!
